channel.title: My IP is messed up
channel.description: I know what is wrong with my server problem that I have been stumped by for a while, and it is my IP. I can ping my IP perfectly, while others cant and it seems like it does not exist. How would I fix this problem? Just for tests, my IP is 67.191.254.68 for tests, but Im not sure why no one except me can ping it. If any of you know how you would fix this, please help. Thanks.

item.dc:creator: @Thrasher_Alpha Thrasher Alpha
item.description:
@Thrasher_Alpha wrote:

[quote=“iKillAssassins, post:43, topic:252847”]… His IP is perfectly ping-able, I just tried it.

EDIT: If for some reason the 3 pings I just did (each was the 4 packet default ping on the IP you put in the first post) were just a fluke, the only few reasons that your IP can’t be pinged would be:

-You have a firewall, antivirus, or other security measure blocking certain packets to avoid vulnerabilities and attacks.

-You aren’t online.

-They’re typing the ping syntax or your IP wrong. (Stupid mistake)

Pings should work 100% of the time that you’re online.[/quote]

I also tested that on a website, it worked. Though my server still isnt working when I try it.
